    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.25a-25b_0001-2"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">25a</fw>
                
                <fw  type="letterhead">
                    Karl <hi rend="caps">H.</hi> Plesse
                        <lb/>
                
                    Bremerhaven-G., den 
                        <lb/>
                    Am Bürgerpark 11
                        <lb/>
                    Fernruf 2212
                        <lb/>
                    Bankkonto: Geestemünder Bank
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Nov. 8, 1957</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>the only way to make up for my delay in writing to you lies in telling you that I have been hard at work translating "when the tree flowered." A work which contains endless excitement and fun for me. I hope to be able to submit the completed translation to you around Xmas, if nothing unforeseen interferes. The process of translating is fascinating. The characters and happenings have such a disturbing reality that you just don't get rid of them once they got you in their clasp.
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.25a-25b_0002"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">25b</fw>
                
                And they certainly got me. I only hope that you will be satisfied with my work. The return to Germany &#8212; only two weeks ago because it had been delayed by an appointment as an interpreter for the Dep. of State &#8212; was quite a change. Gradualy I became accustomed again to the old surroundings though, but the desire to go back to the States, if only for a visit, will certainly remain. I hope that you and your family are in good health and shall be very good to hear from you</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With Kind regards</salute>
                    <salute>Yours</salute>
                
                    <signed>Karl H. Plesse</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
